    <text>
      <body>
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>The Grammar School | Lichfield</placeName>
                    <date>6 June 1856</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                  <p>I am in communication with M <hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Barthropp of Cretingham Rookery nr Woodbridge relative to placing with him as a farm pupil my third son.</p>
                  <p>Do you happen to know any thing of him as a practical Farmer. He is a member of the Council of the Royal A Society of England.</p>
                  <p>Since I last wrote to you I have again after 14 years Exile in the Isle of Man got settled in England having held the Mastership of this School for the last year &amp; a half.</p>
                  <p>I have more chance now of occasionally seeing my friends as we have rail communication to all parts, being on the direct line from London North.</p>
                  <p>Believe me Dear Sir | very faithfully yrs | J G Cumming</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
      </body>
